Some kind of embedded stuff with online interface.
Because it can fairly control anything remotely.
A linux machine with apache, python, motion & arduino IDE.
less than 300 Rs for now,considering we have in built web cam.
It is an open-source electronics prototyping platform.The hardware
reference designs (CAD files) are available under open-source license.
In fact, one can use any microcontroller. Arduino is very easy to use
development board, it has lot of examples and support. And the best part,
we don't have to remember hardware details.
There is 'Pinguino' for PIC, 'Arduino Due' for ARM. The arduino programming
language is compatible with many such controllers.
CGI stands for Common Gateway Interface, it's a standard for
interfacing external applications with web servers.
Readable code and lot of support in web.
C, C++, Perl, PHP, TCL, Shell etc.
A much easier PCB designing tool, which creates PCB and Schematic layout
based on the circuit assembled on virtual breadboard.
It has good support for arduino, one can make shields easily. Very easy to learn,
previous CAD exposure is not required.
I don't see any better alternative for fritzing. But if your product requires
more than two layers and complex routing then KiCAD can serve you better.
It is a video server which uses video4linux to detect motion. With motion
one can capture video/jpeg to stream or to store as video file.
Works out of the box. Simple & lightweight. Saves memory,
invokes server only when change in frame or any motion is detected.
Fortunately there is a better configurable alternative to motion, ffserver.
It comes with ffmpeg package. I will certainly recommend ffserver for its scalability.

Enough of Gyaan, let's get busy.
The best approach would be testing Arduino LED program without apache
& motion.First we need to be sure that we can control LED with serial
communication. We need to write arduino code for the hardware and system
side code in python(one can choose any language).
Now, as our LED can be controlled by python, then think of controlling
that LED over a network. That's it. Your job is done.
There are multiple ways to do so. But, we will use CGI script(test.html) to host our python
code and also to provide a simple html buttons to control.
Run apache to serve your remote requests.
Now we can control the LED remotely, but we don't have any visual confirmation. Add your
web cam. Integrated web cam will also work.

One can use this template for any type of control mechanism. All you need
is your imagination. Think of anything which has an analog or digital output.
Write to me for any suggestion or help at srikant@fossee.in .

Though arduino development board is open source, but still it cost around 1200 Rs.
The reason is simple, it is a development board, it carries more than a LED control circuit.
